    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6536</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AWW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Andrews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jassy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 21, 2.45
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Inform Department that I have received official information that the Ministry for
                    Foreign Affairs and Diplomatic Corps will leave towards the end of the week for
                    Kherson, Russia. This is merely a measure of precaution. It is expected that
                    most of the Government will remain at Jassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrews</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
